    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Some more improvements, mostly making use of Hugo's features.\n\n- [ ] [`layouts/doc/user/single.html`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/blob/master/layouts/doc/user/single.html) should make use of [`layouts/baseof.html`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/blob/master/layouts/baseof.html) in order to have the things like the normal nav bar on the doc pages.\n- [ ] There is no reason that [`content/posts`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/tree/master/content/posts) exists while all posts get a permalink of `/news/`. Just put the posts under `content/news/` and cleanup the permalinks from the front matter (and from hugo.toml). Extra: create a new \"archetype\" for it to enable `hugo new content content/news/...`.\n- [ ] The `active` param in the front matter seems to do nothing. My guess is that it's used for highlighting the currently active nav item. Just use some clever Hugo code for highlighting the right menu item.\n- [ ] Images in [`static/images`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/tree/master/static/images) could potentially be moved to make use of [Page Bundles](https://gohugo.io/content-management/page-bundles/#article). Makes it clear to which page the image belongs and easier to cleanup the website when needed.\n- [ ] Sponsors can be generated from a data file with each entry having a name, logo, desc, etc. Probably easier to maintain than in HTML.\n- [ ] `content/doc/_index.html` can be converted to Markdown.",
